":"1479","1556":"1556","1478":"1478","1554":"1554","1530":"1530","Abt 1462":"circa 1462","1485":"1485","after 1485":"na 1485","1429":"1429","Middlesex, England":"Middlesex, England","Knole, Chevening, Kent, England":"Chevening, Kent, England","Chevening, Kent, England":"Chevening, Kent, England","Heathfield, Sussex, England":"Heathfield, Sussex, England","Sevenoaks, Kent, England":"Sevenoaks, Kent, England"},"en":{"1459–1530":"1459–1530","1458–1485":"1458–1485","1479–1554":"1479–1554","1482–1554":"1482–1554","1483–1556":"1483–1556","1429–1462":"1429–1462","1462":"1462","1483":"1483","1482":"1482","1459":"1459","1458":"1458","1479":"1479","1556":"1556","1478":"1478","1554":"1554","1530":"1530","Abt 1462":"about 1462","1485":"1485","after 1485":"after 1485","1429":"1429","Middlesex, England":"Middlesex, England","Knole, Chevening, Kent, England":"Chevening, Kent, England","Chevening, Kent, England":"Chevening, Kent, England","Heathfield, Sussex, England":"Heathfield, Sussex, England","Sevenoaks, Kent, England":"Sevenoaks, Kent, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lennard","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Leonard  .","Americanized form of German   Lennert   or of some other similar (like-sounding) surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Leonard","meanings":["English; French (<b>Léonard</b>); Walloon (mainly <b>Léonard</b>): from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>leo</i> ‘lion’ (a late addition to the vocabulary of ancient Germanic name elements, taken from Latin) + <i>hard</i> ‘hardy, brave, strong’, which was taken to England by the Normans. A Christian saint of this name, who is supposed to have lived in the 6th century, but about whom nothing is known except for a largely fictional life dating from half a millennium later, was popular throughout Europe in the early Middle Ages and was regarded as the patron of peasants and horses. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed cognates from other languages, e.g. Italian   Leonardo  , Polish, Slovenian, etc.   Lenart   or   Lenard  , and probably also their derivatives. Compare   Larned  ,   Learned  , and   Yenor  .","Irish (Fermanagh): adopted as an English equivalent of Gaelic <b>Mac Giolla Fhionáin</b> or of   Langan  .","German: variant of   Leonhard  , cognate with 1 above."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir John Lennard was born in 1459, in Chevening, Kent, England as the son of George Lennard Esquire. He married Lady Mary Anne Byrd in 1478, in Middlesex, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1530, in his hometown, at the age of 71."},"et":{"1459–1530":"1459–1530","1458–1485":"1458–1485","1479–1554":"1479–1554","1482–1554":"1482–1554","1483–1556":"1483–1556","1429–1462":"1429–1462","1462":"1462","1483":"1483","1482":"1482","1459":"1459","1458":"1458","1479":"1479","1556":"1556","1478":"1478","1554":"1554","1530":"1530","Abt 1462":"umbes 1462","1485":"1485","after 1485":"pärast 1485","1429":"1429","Middlesex, England":"Middlesex, England","Knole, Chevening, Kent, England":"Chevening, Kent, England","Chevening, Kent, England":"Chevening, Kent, England","Heathfield, Sussex, England":"Heathfield, Sussex, England","Sevenoaks, Kent, England":"Sevenoaks, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1459–1530":"1459–1530","1458–1485":"1458–1485","1479–1554":"1479–1554","1482–1554":"1482–1554","1483–1556":"1483–1556","1429–1462":"1429–1462","1462":"1462","1483":"1483","1482":"1482","1459":"1459","1458":"1458","1479":"1479","1556":"1556","1478":"1478","1554":"1554","1530":"1530",